@larryfish-man It isn't ridiculous to want to see plot points they previously show get wrapped up properly. It is bad writing to have a set up with no pay off.
Is it worth getting riled up that people want the multi hundred million dollar budget show to have better quality for its production value than it does? 
Apathy towards shitty writing is what's going to end up killing off good stories, it's already pretty much there.

@lyndy101 Am I wrong?  Maybe you should be.  The only father-figures in the entire series who were given any degree of respect were Hopper and Bob, probably in both cases because they were willing to assume fatherly responsibilities for other men's children.  That is the only adult male role that our current media culture is willing to find at least _somewhat_ acceptable.
Even in those cases, both characters were portrayed as having serious flaws (Hopper) and/or were objects of ridicule (Bob), though they also were allowed some moments to shine.  
Contrast that with how any of the adult women in the series (Karen, Joyce, Terry, Becky, Claudia, etc.) are portrayed.  Do _they_ have any serious character flaws?  Joyce's biggest vice is _smoking_ when she's under stress, and I can't think of anything worse than that for any of them.

