The reason you think shadow mind flayer was strong was because you assume that it literally created the upside down as in created an entire universe when that was never suggested to be the case. Mind flayer never showed to conquer multiple worlds or dimensions, nothing like that.

@daveweisbrich1769 exactly. shows like this make the mistakes of taking themselves too seriously when they see success, and trying to answer questions the writers clearly cannot answer well while also keeping the mystery and intrigue of the show.

shows like these are meant to stay elusive and abstract, posing legit questions based on visual clues, lines and actions, but allowing the audiance to answer them for themselves and make their own conclusions and connections (that still in the grand scheme of things make sense). kind of like twin peaks.

the first season of the show managed to retain that abstract element while being entertaining and posing interesting questions, but everything else after is them trying to turn it into a regular show to get more people hooked.

